WEBVTT

00:00.271 --> 00:01.638
My name
is Michael Westen.

00:02.047 --> 00:04.081
I used to be
a spy until...

00:04.432 --> 00:05.515
We got a burn notice on you.

00:05.566 --> 00:07.401
You're blacklisted.

00:07.485 --> 00:09.853
When you're burned,
you've got nothing--

00:09.904 --> 00:12.072
no cash, no credit,
no job history.

00:12.156 --> 00:14.441
You're stuck in whatever city
they decide to dump you in.

00:14.525 --> 00:16.860
- Where am I?
- Miami.

00:16.911 --> 00:19.196
You do whatever work
comes your way.

00:19.247 --> 00:21.365
You rely on anyone
who's still talking to you...

00:22.867 --> 00:23.834
A trigger-happy girlfriend...

00:23.901 --> 00:25.252
Should we shoot them?

00:25.336 --> 00:27.254
An old friend who used
to inform on you to the FBI...

00:27.338 --> 00:29.906
You know spies--
bunch of bitchy little girls.

00:29.957 --> 00:31.291
Family too...

00:31.376 --> 00:32.241
Hey, is that your mom again?

00:32.293 --> 00:33.410
If you're desperate...

00:33.461 --> 00:34.741
Someone needs your help,
Michael.

00:34.762 --> 00:37.431
And a down-and-out spy
you met along the way.

00:37.515 --> 00:39.016
That's how we do it,
people.

00:39.083 --> 00:41.751
Bottom line,
as long as you're burned,

00:41.803 --> 00:44.755
you're not going anywhere.

00:45.022 --> 00:46.473
It's a deep-cover job,

00:46.557 --> 00:48.008
going after the leader
of a terrorist network.

00:48.092 --> 00:50.927
I need you to bring them down,
no matter what.

00:50.978 --> 00:53.647
I'm James.
Welcome to the family.

00:53.731 --> 00:55.131
This guy, James--
he's getting to you.

00:55.182 --> 00:56.816
They all are.

00:56.901 --> 00:58.801
It's difficult to work so hard
to be part of something,

00:58.853 --> 01:00.403
knowing you have
to destroy it.

01:00.471 --> 01:01.905
These people believe
in what they're doing.

01:01.972 --> 01:03.940
The data you ripped from
Sonya's phone was a gold mine.

01:03.991 --> 01:05.909
- So we know where James is?
- No.

01:05.976 --> 01:07.310
But for the first time,
we know where he's gonna be

01:07.361 --> 01:10.030
before he gets there--
Veracruz, Mexico.

01:17.955 --> 01:19.989
Alpha team,
I'm a friendly.

01:20.041 --> 01:22.208
- Hey!
- Simon.

01:22.293 --> 01:24.761
I'm running this extraction,
on orders of the CIA.

01:24.828 --> 01:26.329
You're working
with a monster!

01:26.380 --> 01:28.548
And what is Michael, huh?

01:28.633 --> 01:32.001
No, no, no, no, no, no.

01:33.354 --> 01:35.338
Only two people in the world
knew exactly

01:35.389 --> 01:36.806
where we'd be today.

01:36.857 --> 01:39.142
Me...

01:39.193 --> 01:40.477
And you.

01:40.528 --> 01:42.062
I would never betray you.

01:42.146 --> 01:45.532
I'm gonna give you
five seconds to come clean

01:45.616 --> 01:47.567
before this becomes
a lot more painful.

01:47.652 --> 01:50.153
She didn't betray you.
I did.

01:50.204 --> 01:52.055
I'm working with the CIA.

01:54.625 --> 01:57.327
A spy's job,
at the most basic level,

01:57.378 --> 01:59.212
is to deceive.

01:59.297 --> 02:00.630
You build a lie.

02:00.681 --> 02:03.550
You nurture that lie,
selling it to your target,

02:03.634 --> 02:06.002
bit by bit,
until he believes.

02:06.053 --> 02:09.439
Your lie becomes your weapon,
your salvation,

02:09.507 --> 02:14.227
the only thing that stands
between you and disaster.

02:14.312 --> 02:16.480
When that lie falls away,

02:16.531 --> 02:18.532
you're left
with only the hard truth

02:18.616 --> 02:20.567
of who you are
and what you've done.

02:20.651 --> 02:22.319
When that happens,
you're out of moves.

02:22.370 --> 02:26.239
The only thing there is
to do then is await your fate.

02:26.324 --> 02:29.042
Come on.
James wants to talk.

02:36.667 --> 02:39.636
I want you
to tell me something.

02:39.703 --> 02:42.372
Was any of it real?

02:42.423 --> 02:44.391
Between us?

02:47.228 --> 02:50.547
I had a job to do, Sonya--

02:50.598 --> 02:54.434
get close to you, close
to the people you work with.

02:54.519 --> 02:56.403
You didn't answer
the question.

03:01.409 --> 03:04.778
I was undercover for so long,
I lost track of who I was.

03:07.498 --> 03:08.731
And part of me--

03:08.783 --> 03:12.068
the part that believed
in what we were doing--

03:12.119 --> 03:14.254
that part...

03:16.407 --> 03:19.092
cared for you.

03:19.177 --> 03:22.429
And you?

03:22.513 --> 03:26.433
Were you just recruiting
an asset?

03:26.517 --> 03:29.052
I had a job to do too.

03:29.103 --> 03:32.422
Did I take pleasure in it?
Yes.

03:32.473 --> 03:35.609
My heart belongs to my work.

03:35.693 --> 03:38.361
It will always come first.

